Author: FINLAYSON
Vol / Page: 119
Edition: 1979
Quote: When we gets the old gig properly worked over everything should be pie-on. <i>Ibid.</i> 124 `Well,' thinks Jake, `this is a nice sort of hitch. Just as we were getting everything pie-on as Uncle Ted calls it.' <i>Ibid.</i> 151 `Surely the gig's properly set up now, Uncle Ted,' he says. `Everything's what you call pie-on.' <i>Ibid.</i> 166 When we gets the old gig properly worked over everything should be pie-on.
